[[File:Gakko_Bosatsu_Hokkedo.JPG|thumb|right|Gakkō bosatsu, [[Nara period]], [[Tōdai-ji]], [[Nara, Nara|Nara]]]]
'''Candraprabha''' (literally "Moonlight", {{cjkv|r=Gakkō bosatsu|p=Yuèguāng púsà|c=月光菩薩}}) is a [[bodhisattva]] often seen with [[Suryaprabha]], as the two siblings serve [[Bhaisajyaguru]]. Statues of Nikkō and Gakko closely resemble each other and are commonly found together, sometimes flanking temple doors. They are also known in mainland Asia as [[Deva (Buddhism)|devas]] rather than bodhisattvas.

